00:00:13.700 --> 00:00:16.700
 who decides what is not carcinogenic, 

00:00:16.700 --> 00:00:20.460
 has issued a statement that alcoholic beverages - all alcoholic beverages - 

00:00:20.460 --> 00:00:23.740
 should be considered carcinogenic to humans. 

00:00:23.742 --> 00:00:26.977
 The latest research has focused on acetaldehyde, 

00:00:26.977 --> 00:00:31.730
 the first and most toxic alcohol metabolite as a cancer agent. 

00:00:31.730 --> 00:00:37.460
 The bacteria in our mouth seem to oxidize alcohol to a carcinogen 

00:00:37.460 --> 00:00:40.712
 called acetaldehyde, which we then swallow. 

00:00:40.712 --> 00:00:42.720
 There is convincing evidence 

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:45.720
 that alcohol consumption increases the risk of breast cancer 

00:00:45.720 --> 00:00:47.650
 but most of the data were obtained from studies 

00:00:47.650 --> 00:00:51.440
 which have focused on the impact of moderate or high alcohol intake, 

00:00:51.440 --> 00:00:54.500
 while we know little about mild drinking, 

00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:57.140
