00:01:06.046 --> 00:01:09.206
 more than hundreds of studies. 

00:01:09.636 --> 00:01:13.864
 It is estimated that approximately 5,000 deaths from breast cancer per year 

00:01:13.864 --> 00:01:16.024
 can be attributed to drinking a small amount of alcohol, 

00:01:16.024 --> 00:01:19.762
 which means that nearly 5,000 women who have died of breast cancer 

00:01:19.762 --> 00:01:21.052
 maybe they didn't have to die 

00:01:21.052 --> 00:01:24.109
 if alcohol consumption is completely avoided. 

00:01:24.109 --> 00:01:27.160
 That is why the editorial was published by Breast, 

00:01:27.160 --> 00:01:28.160
 who concluded: 

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:31.737
 "Women who regularly consume alcohol have an increased risk of breast cancer 

00:01:31.737 --> 00:01:35.153
 which is dose-dependent, but without a threshold, " 

00:01:35.153 --> 00:01:38.423
 which means that there is apparently no level of alcohol consumption, 

00:01:38.423 --> 00:01:41.580
 which at least minimizes the risk of breast cancer. 

00:01:41.580 --> 00:01:44.250
